# ── Authentication (Better Auth + Google OAuth) ─────────────────────
# BETTER_AUTH_SECRET=<openssl rand -base64 32>
# BETTER_AUTH_URL=http://localhost:3000
# GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=your-client-id.apps.googleusercontent.com
# GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET=your-client-secret
#
# Comma-separated Better Auth user IDs treated as admin regardless of
# their stored role. Use to bootstrap the first admin.
# ADMIN_USER_IDS=

# ── Vercel AI Gateway API key ───────────────────────────────────────
# The ONE credential for every LLM call: the Solutions Architect (Anthropic
# Opus), the Gemini document summarizer, and the offline scripts
# (test-schema.ts, sync-knowledge.ts, preview-attachment-condense.ts). Model
# ids use the gateway's `creator/model-name` format (see lib/models.ts), so
# switching models never needs new provider wiring or keys.
#
# Create a key in the Vercel dashboard: AI Gateway → API keys. (OIDC auth is
# Vercel-deployment-only; on Cloud Run + local dev the API key is the path.)
# Required for the document-attachment path too: the upload-time extract route
# (POST /api/media/[assetId]/extract) hard-fails (502, the file manager shows
# "Retry") without it, and the chat's lazy backstop degrades to a "couldn't be
# read" placeholder. Wired onto the Cloud Run revision in prod.
# AI_GATEWAY_API_KEY=vck_your-key-here

# ── Firestore (persistence layer) ───────────────────────────────────
# Required on Cloud Run (auto-detected from the metadata server).
# Local dev points at the dedicated dev project so dev data (users,
# apps, media rows) never mixes with production. Your `gcloud auth
# application-default login` identity needs access to it.
# GOOGLE_CLOUD_PROJECT=commcare-nova-dev
#
# Set to use the Firestore emulator instead of a real project.
# The SDK connects to the emulator automatically when this is set.
# FIRESTORE_EMULATOR_HOST=localhost:8080

# ── Multimedia (GCS) ────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Bucket holding media bytes — required by the media upload/read routes.
# Production (`nova-multimedia-prod`) is wired onto the Cloud Run revision
# via `gcloud run services update`. In prod the runtime service account holds
# `roles/storage.objectUser` on the bucket plus `serviceAccountTokenCreator`
# on itself (for V4 signed-URL signing); both are already granted.
#
# Local dev uses the dev project's bucket through the SAME client and
# credentials path as Firestore (ADC). The one dev difference: browser
# uploads PUT to the same-origin `/api/media/upload/dev-put` route instead
# of a V4 signed URL, because developer ADC has no signing key — see
# `lib/storage/media.ts::createSignedUploadUrl`.
NOVA_MEDIA_BUCKET=commcare-nova-dev-multimedia

# ── Case store (Postgres) ───────────────────────────────────────────
# Local dev: connects the case store to the docker-compose Postgres that
# `npm run dev` boots (compose.yaml). When set, the app uses a plain pg
# connection at this URL instead of the Cloud SQL connector — an explicit
# opt-in, so production (which never sets it) still requires the NOVA_DB_*
# vars below. Must match compose.yaml's user / password / db.
NOVA_DB_LOCAL_URL=postgres://nova:nova@localhost:5432/nova_cases?sslmode=disable
#
# Production only (wired onto the Cloud Run revision via
# `gcloud run services update`): the Cloud SQL connector reads these. Leave
# unset locally — NOVA_DB_LOCAL_URL takes precedence.
# NOVA_DB_NAME=
# NOVA_DB_USER=
# NOVA_DB_INSTANCE_CONNECTION_NAME=

# ── Confluence knowledge sync (optional) ────────────────────────────
# Only needed for scripts/sync-knowledge.ts
# CONFLUENCE_BASE_URL=https://api.atlassian.com/ex/confluence/your-cloud-id/wiki
# CONFLUENCE_EMAIL=you@example.com
# CONFLUENCE_API_TOKEN=your-token-here
# RATE_LIMIT_MS=100
# TRIAGE_BATCH_SIZE=5

# ── Google Maps (GPS location picker, builder preview) ──────────────
# BOTH vars are required to enable the map; with either missing, the geopoint
# picker degrades to manual lat/lon entry. They are NEXT_PUBLIC_, so they're
# inlined into the client bundle at BUILD time — prod must set them when the
# image is built, not just at Cloud Run runtime.
#
# Browser key for the Maps JavaScript API + Places API (New) + Geocoding API.
# A PUBLIC, referrer-restricted key (exposed in the bundle by design — secured
# by HTTP-referrer + per-API restrictions). Use a SEPARATE key per environment:
# this local key is restricted to localhost referrers; prod uses its own key
# (restricted to commcare.app origins) sourced from Secret Manager at build.
# Create/manage in the commcare-nova GCP project's API Credentials.
# NEXT_PUBLIC_GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY=AIza...
#
# Vector Map ID (Cloud Console → Maps → Map Management, type JavaScript /
# Vector) — required: the picker runs a WebGL vector basemap + the modern
# draggable Advanced Marker, which needs a Map ID. Same GCP project as the key.
# NEXT_PUBLIC_GOOGLE_MAPS_MAP_ID=
